 "logTail": [
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"The board has heard it. That serves for witness.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "He opens the day-book to a page already half-filled with other men.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "On the veranda above the step, Naoyuki has stopped — the second son, papers of his own under one arm. Passing, and made a witness like the rest of the room.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"The house is glad of —\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Naoyuki"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "The sentence stops. He stands with it a moment, as if he has read it back and found it not worth the ink.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Two hands left. You were here. That is all it is.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Naoyuki"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "He goes on along the veranda. He looked at you once.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Then Genemon takes up the brush, and asks it plainly, at board volume. The room hears without listening.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"One thing before the ink. If a claim follows you here, I enter it against your board. Is anything owing on you?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"And if there were?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Then the house's claim comes first, while you eat its rice. After that — whoever can find you. So far nobody has asked.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "You begin to mark the turning of the days, and the four seasons with them.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "milestone",
   "text": "Rank ↑ — The day-hand 日雇",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "The outer court of the guest house, where the day's work is set out and seen to — set out in the dark now, the days being what they are, and often finished in it. Genemon's lamp is lit before the sky is; what is done here still gets written down.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "The forecourt"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "The estate's face, kept barely, kept anyway: snow is swept from between the gateposts before anyone can see it lying there. Yohei's stall still comes on market days, smaller, and leaves while there is light to walk home by.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "The gate & gateyard"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "The outer court of the guest house, where the day's work is set out and seen to — set out in the dark now, the days being what they are, and often finished in it. Genemon's lamp is lit before the sky is; what is done here still gets written down.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "The forecourt"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "A mat, a chipped bowl, a nail for the coat, in the lean space between woodpiles — and the piles are the winter's work made visible, burned down armload by armload. The widening of your corner is the one count on the estate that runs your way.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "The woodshed"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "The outer court of the guest house, where the day's work is set out and seen to — set out in the dark now, the days being what they are, and often finished in it. Genemon's lamp is lit before the sky is; what is done here still gets written down.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "The forecourt"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "The guest house's skirts, the paddy and the rows that pay for everything else. Winter lays the fields off — stubble, frost, the water let out — and moves their work indoors: the tools that will open them again are mended now or not at all.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "The home paddy & vegetable rows"
